<% content_for :title, "Setup Guide - North Coast Rails Workshop" %>

<div class="card">
  <h1>Development Environment Setup</h1>
  
  <p class="lead">
    Choose your operating system below for detailed setup instructions. We'll help you install 
    Ruby, Rails, and all the tools you need to start building web applications.
  </p>

  <div class="highlight">
    <h3>‚ö° Quick Check</h3>
    <p>If you already have a development environment, check if you have:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Ruby 3.0 or higher</li>
      <li>Rails 7.0 or higher</li>
      <li>Git version control</li>
      <li>A text editor or IDE</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="setup-options">
  <div class="card">
    <h2>ü™ü Windows Setup</h2>
    <p>Best option: Use Windows Subsystem for Linux (WSL) for a Unix-like development environment.</p>
    
    <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
    <div class="highlight">
      <h4>Check Your Windows Version</h4>
      <p>Press <code>Windows + R</code>, type <code>winver</code>, and press Enter.</p>
      <p><strong>Required:</strong> Windows 10 version 2004 and higher (Build 19041 and higher) or Windows 11.</p>
    </div>

    <h3>Step 1: Install WSL 2</h3>
    <pre><code># Open PowerShell as Administrator and run:
wsl --install

# This will install WSL 2 with Ubuntu by default
# Restart your computer when prompted</code></pre>

    <h3>Step 2: Setup Ubuntu</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Open "Ubuntu" from Start Menu</li>
      <li>Create a username and password</li>
      <li>Update the system:</li>
    </ul>
    <pre><code>sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y</code></pre>

    <h3>Step 3: Install Development Tools</h3>
    <pre><code># Install essential build tools
sudo apt install -y curl git build-essential

# Install Ruby using rbenv
curl -fsSL https://github.com/rbenv/rbenv-installer/raw/HEAD/bin/rbenv-installer | bash

# Add rbenv to your PATH
echo 'export PATH="$HOME/.rbenv/bin:$PATH"' >> ~/.bashrc
echo 'eval "$(rbenv init -)"' >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc

# Install Ruby
rbenv install 3.2.3
rbenv global 3.2.3

# Install Rails
gem install rails</code></pre>

    <h3>Step 4: Install a Text Editor</h3>
    <p>We recommend <strong>Visual Studio Code</strong> with the WSL extension:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Download VS Code from <a href="https://code.visualstudio.com/">https://code.visualstudio.com/</a></li>
      <li>Install the "WSL" extension</li>
      <li>Open your project folder with <code>code .</code> from WSL terminal</li>
    </ul>

    <%= link_to "Detailed Windows Guide", "#", class: "btn" %>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>üçé macOS Setup</h2>
    <p>Use Homebrew package manager for easy installation of development tools.</p>
    
    <h3>Step 1: Install Homebrew</h3>
    <pre><code>/bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"</code></pre>

    <h3>Step 2: Install Development Tools</h3>
    <pre><code># Install Git
brew install git

# Install rbenv for Ruby version management
brew install rbenv

# Setup rbenv
echo 'eval "$(rbenv init -)"' >> ~/.zshrc
source ~/.zshrc

# Install Ruby
rbenv install 3.2.3
rbenv global 3.2.3

# Install Rails
gem install rails</code></pre>

    <h3>Step 3: Text Editor</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>VS Code:</strong> <code>brew install --cask visual-studio-code</code></li>
      <li><strong>Sublime Text:</strong> <code>brew install --cask sublime-text</code></li>
      <li><strong>Atom:</strong> <code>brew install --cask atom</code></li>
    </ul>

    <%= link_to "Detailed macOS Guide", "#", class: "btn" %>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>üêß Linux Setup</h2>
    <p>Instructions for Ubuntu/Debian-based distributions.</p>
    
    <h3>Step 1: Update System</h3>
    <pre><code>sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y</code></pre>

    <h3>Step 2: Install Dependencies</h3>
    <pre><code>sudo apt install -y curl git build-essential libssl-dev libreadline-dev zlib1g-dev</code></pre>

    <h3>Step 3: Install Ruby</h3>
    <pre><code># Install rbenv
curl -fsSL https://github.com/rbenv/rbenv-installer/raw/HEAD/bin/rbenv-installer | bash

# Setup rbenv
echo 'export PATH="$HOME/.rbenv/bin:$PATH"' >> ~/.bashrc
echo 'eval "$(rbenv init -)"' >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc

# Install Ruby
rbenv install 3.2.3
rbenv global 3.2.3

# Install Rails
gem install rails</code></pre>

    <%= link_to "Detailed Linux Guide", "#", class: "btn" %>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <h2>üîç Verify Your Installation</h2>
  <p>After completing the setup for your operating system, verify everything works:</p>
  
  <pre><code># Check Ruby version
ruby --version
# Should show Ruby 3.2.3 or higher

# Check Rails version  
rails --version
# Should show Rails 7.0 or higher

# Check Git
git --version
# Should show Git version info</code></pre>

  <div class="highlight">
    <h3>Next Steps</h3>
    <p>Once your environment is set up:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Clone this workshop repository</li>
      <li>Navigate to the Workshop Steps to start building</li>
      <li>Join our community for support and questions</li>
    </ol>
    
    <%= link_to "Continue to Workshop ‚Üí", workshop_steps_path, class: "btn" %>
  </div>
</div>

